data.title: Trespass (2011)
data.meta_description: written by: Karl Gajdusek produced by: Boaz Davidson, Avi Lerner, David Winkler & Irwin Winkler directed by: Joel Schaumacher rating: R (for violence and terror, pervasive language and some brief drug use) runtime: 91 min. U.S. release date: September 21, 2001 (Toronto Film Festival, VOD & iTunes) & October 14, 2011 (limited)   DVD &…
data.text:
Windi permalink

I haven’t enjoyed a Nicholas Cage movie in ages…. Or Nicole Kidman for that matter. I don’t think either of those would entice me to see a movie. The whole idea of a home invasion movie has been done and overdone, Another reason for me not to bother!

Brian permalink

I haven’t subjected myself to the celluloid feces that is a Schaumacher movie since 8mm. You’ve just confirmed what I’ve already know for well over a decade. He is incapable of making a movie that doesn’t make you want to gouge your own eyes out. Thanks for taking one for the team!
